The article discusses the United States' response to the severe flooding in Pakistan in 2010. President Obama directed his administration to assist the Pakistani people in dealing with this humanitarian crisis. The US government provided financial aid, food, shelter, medical supplies, and other necessary items. They also delivered halal meals, pre-fabricated bridges, rescue boats, water filtration units, and a generator to support flood relief efforts. US helicopters and military aircraft were deployed to rescue stranded citizens and transport supplies to affected areas. Additional US personnel were sent to work alongside Pakistani officials to coordinate relief efforts and assess recovery needs. The US government emphasized the need for international cooperation and pledged to continue assisting Pakistan in responding to the crisis.